"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Tiny airport for a big city.  I flew in from LAX to Frankfurt to TXL on Luftansa.  My boyfriend and I had to store our luggage on a different part of the plane, so we chose to wait until everyone got off before getting our carry on luggage.<br><br>As we disembarked, I thought it was odd that I could still hear talking.  Maybe its people waiting in the terminal to board the next plane?  No, it was people waiting to claim their check luggage!!   Unlike many bigger airports, the claim luggage is just steps from the gate.<br><br>It took a while to get our luggage, we found the exit, and found an Information Kiosk to get tourist tickets for the museum and public transportation.<br><br>After getting our tourist tickets, we found the island for the taxi, and took it to our hotel.<br><br>Very simple, very small, and easy.  There&#39;s cash machines located near the information kiosk, and snack places to get a drink or food.<br><br>I do not think they&#39;re free wifi but I wasn&#39;t there long enough to find out.",
