"reviewcomment":"KaDeWe is a bit like Harrod&#39;s in London - you can find just about anything you need here. I was at the post office across the square from KaDeWe and needed a tube to mail some posters that I purchased from the Helmut Newtown foundation near the Zoo station. The post office didn&#39;t sell poster tubes but the helpful Beamter told me to try KaDeWe. Sure enough, on one of the top floors is a great stationary section that sells *everything* you&#39;d ever need for writing/mailing/recording stuff. I found the tube I needed, bought tape and felt tip pen - the store personnel helped me even pack the tube which I took back to the post office to mail to the States. Great experience. <br><br>The food hall at KaDeWe is amazing and the luggage section has a good selection of the German-made &#34;Rimowa&#34; brand aluminum suitcases. There&#39;s also a branch of the Dolores Mexican restaurant nearby and an excellent organic sausage stand near the entrance to the subway (if you don&#39;t want to eat at the food hall). Highly recommended.",
