"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/KykpLXbuiYZOHcfCYS0-_Q/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"My Oh My! Seeing Berlin from foot is one awesome thing but seeing the whole city from above is stunning! You not only get to see one portion of Berlin, but the whole 360! <br>I recommend coming during the afternoon, one reason being it is not too hot and you get awesome lighting and you get to see the sunset of course (depends on the time of year you are coming though)! When you buy your ticket you wait in a long line but it feels like it goes by fast because you are too busy looking at other tourists. Once you buy your ticket there is about a 2 hour wait to get to go to the top. If you want to eat inside the restaurant make you book your reservation head of time. Meanwhile you wait, there are couches and seat with tables to socialize or drink a cup of coffee. The you go up a crowded elevator ride to the very top. This part is exciting because your ears close up from the high elevation and speed. Once your up there, take your time and enjoy the view! you are not timed so you can pretty much stay up there as long as you like. <br>There is a bar with food service in the viewing section which I thought was good. The food was delicious and the bartender was friendly. I also recommend drinking a beer while you are up here, it&#39;s quite peaceful. :)",
