"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/76F4fQI9Eo0Go_FZC_Ks6w/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Okay, I have a confession to make. I have a true, deep, and undying love for... currywurst. I knew it before I visited Berlin, having fallen in love with it on the side of a mountain near Neuschwanstein when I visited Bavaria and Munich a few years ago. But, coming back to Germany for the first time since, I needed more. Lots more! (For posterity, because even though I have an addiction and I&#39;m not ready to go into recovery, I&#39;d better be honest: I had six currywurst in three days in Berlin...!)<br><br>Konnopke Imbiss is listed on most sites, including Yelp, as a Must-Do if you&#39;re a currywurst person, even if your love isn&#39;t as big as mine. When I looked up how close they were to where I was staying, I was even more excited. I immediately walked down and proceeded to order zwei currywurst mit ein klein pommes (two currywurst with one small fries). The total, I remember, was €5.70, which was freakin&#39; amazing, because in London it would have been over £10, which is what, $15 in the US? I love you, Euro. I love you too, currywurst.<br><br>Very, very good, even at 11am on a Monday morning. Great homemade ketchup, crispy fries, and traditional currywurst sausage cooked just right. Served piping hot with wee spear-forks, and all take-away and at a great price.<br><br>Like everyone says, Must Do. (For me, Must Repeat.)",
