"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I just spent one of the most enjoyable days I&#39;ve had in the six months I&#39;ve lived in Berlin. The Erholungspark in Marzahn (Gärten der Welt) costs just 3 Euros and took me a little over an hour to reach by bike from Prenzlauer Berg. Coincidentally, I had just seen an excellent, moving documentary on <a href='/redir?url=http%3A%2F%2Farte.tv&amp;s=ec82febf11f00fa6016fb017cdefb7a7748637005e55f809a12661ec40c5a17a' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>arte.tv</a> yesterday about the challenges young people face today growing up in Marzahn-Hellersdorf, the economically depressed area which surrounds the gardens. Riding through the real East Berlin depicted in this film was an experience. I was happy to see that the residents have access to this lovely park.<br><br> I enjoyed all the different gardens - especially the Korean and Japanese ones. The English labyrinth was great, too. It was a special treat to witness the happy participants of a wedding party and reception taking place in the Chinese Garden. The entire setting was very peaceful and I really liked that there were so many benches and chairs set up to take advantage of the sun, the quiet, and the ambiance. Highly recommended!",
