"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/W8Botg_14DhViADlCNtaZA/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"The wife and I were in Europe for our honeymoon in November 2013, and did some country hopping.  Our primary destinations were France &amp; Italy, but we stayed in Germany a few days because we chose to fly Air Berlin from ORY-TXL and TXL-FCO based on price and membership in Oneworld.  Ironically we liked Germany better than Italy or France, but that&#39;s another story.  <br><br>Air Berlin is an LCC, so you get no frills.  No first class, no IFE, etc.  However, you do get your first check bag free (2nd check bag for nominal fee if purchased online), free soft drinks, free light snack, and options to buy hot meals and alcohol.  <br><br>Our flight from ORY-TXL was aboard one of the airline&#39;s new Boeing 737-800&#39;s with the Boeing Sky Interior.  The flight wasn&#39;t too full, and the young flight crew were very friendly and professional.  <br><br>Our flight from TXL-FCO, on the other hand was aboard an older, worn A320 and was PACKED.  It also had a more senior flight crew was quite unfriendly and rough... But that still didn&#39;t diminish the value of the flight and I would choose to fly with them again in a heartbeat.  <br><br>The one thing I&#39;m not looking forward to is the closure of TXL and transfer of flights to BER.  TXL is REALLY close to downtown Berlin, and while it&#39;s an awful airport, the convenience more than makes up for this.",
