"reviewcomment":"&#39;which market have you visited?&#39; was the question asked most about Berlin. <br>&#39;the one between two churches&#39; we said excitedly, not wanting to butcher the german pronounciation of gendarmenmarkt. <br><br>This market was great, sure a euro to get in, but all in all, it was the one that I went to visit twice because I loved the atmosphere so much, it was like a really nice mix of locals and british tourists, and OMG I LOVED THE CHRISTMAS BAUBLE STORE. I never knew you could have a whole shop dedicated to christmas decorations and ornaments. it was PURE kitsch. <br><br>Do you know what else I loved- the drinks that came with a souvenir mug/glass. They were too adorable. and the hot apple drink was lovely! Talking about drinks, trying to order a half pint in berlin here is hard. They gave me a pint instead. not that i should complain because I ordered a really yummy beer. But it was bigger than the size of my face. and half the size of my body. (TOILETS PLEASE- which is 30 cents....but when you gotta go, you gotta go)<br><br>They also have a stage dedicated to live music- and there was an acapella german man band who did a backstreet boys tribute song, with boyband dance moves. I loved it, it was amazing! (also, it&#39;s really the skinny small guy in the group that has the deepest singing voice- i mean, at least you know there&#39;s a god...)<br><br>This market is also laden with sit down restaurant type booths- and it&#39;s got panes of plastic window to keep the heat in whilst you eat. Definitely recommend the Gendarmenmarkt if you go berlin around Christmas time!",
