"reviewcomment":"I have recently fallen in love with Indian food and part of it is thanks to Amrit. I saw this restaurant when I first arrived in Berlin and was immediately intrigued by the vibrant umbrellas and decor outside of the building (I&#39;m a sucker for presentation).<br><br>At long last, I finally decided to head up to Oranienburger Straße (although there are numerous other locations in Berlin) for lunch at Amrit and was far from disappointed. It was gorgeous out so I sat outside underneath one of their Indian-inspired umbrellas and ordered, challenging myself with a German menu. Clearly my German isn&#39;t perfect so I wasn&#39;t fully certain what I was going to get but my word was it tasty - plenty of spices like good Indian food has.<br><br>One of my biggest complaints about the restaurant is the waiters who stand outside and practically beg you to come eat there. Amrit, you have good food - why not let it speak for itself instead of looking so desperate.",
