"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"We found this restaurant completely by accident. I&#39;d planned out a lot of restaurants to visit in advance but as soon as we got to Berlin we left out hotel room and went for a walk around Mitte to get some food as we were so hungry. We found Augustiner am Gendarmenmarkt and stopped in to grab some food and beer. Wow! It was fantastic. Traditional German pub food and the most delicious beer. This is exactly what I had always wanted from my trip to Germany. The food, drink and atmosphere were all just perfect and this ended up being one of the best places we ate at - completely by accident!<br><br>We visited twice in the end. The first night we had a giant platter of various meats and every single thing was delicious. The second time I had the pork knuckle, a Germany staple that I&#39;d always wanted to try. After some difficulty in working out how to cut into the thing (my fault!) I couldn&#39;t get enough of that either.<br><br>If you like hearty pub food then this is your place. Also, the Augustiner Hell beer is now one of the my absolute favourite drinks of all time. Enjoy!",
