"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/YlEFSVT_OQ1jAhu_aAbQRg/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I was hoping that this restaurant sucked. But unfortunately, I was wrong. <br><br>See, the thing is, I once entered an Ishin before (they are a small chain of sushi restaurants here in Berlin), it was a long time ago (in a galaxy far far away, oh, wait, never mind...), and I went with a colleague for lunch. I was so dissatisfied with it, and vowed never to enter an Ishin again. So I made it my personal goal to try to find the best sushi in Berlin, and I firmly believed that Ishin isn&#39;t the place to look for it.<br><br>Enter my companion, who swears by Ishin. I suppose he was able to convince me to give Ishin a second chance, so tonight, I did. We went on a Thursday (Thursday and Friday are the best days for sushi, by the way, due to the fish shipments), and tried their nigiri menu (for 16,50 EUR, you get to choose 15 pieces). That was a swanky deal. We additionally ordered gyoza, and hiya-yakko.<br><br>And oh my god. That was sushi that can kick ass. They had swanky offerings like uni, toro, amaebi, and others, and the quality of the fish is so evident from the way it melts in your mouth. <br><br>So yes, I give up. Ishin delivers, as long as it is Thursday (or Friday, perhaps), and you&#39;re not getting the lunch menu. It&#39;s a good thing this place is close to where we live.",
