"reviewcomment":"My girlfriend and I went there along with my sister for her birthday dinner. The surroundings which could have been pretty idyllic, are sadly somewhat ruined by a large construction site right next to it. However, these are soon forgotten, as the food arrives. We chose the 8 course surprise menu with wine. This means the chef gets more or less free hands, but some of the courses are the same ones as on the 6 course tasting menu. The highlight was the eel with smoked pork bellies and eel tea, but all 8 courses were great tasting, all the way from the amuse bouche through to the surprise dessert consisting of no less than 8 tiny dessert dishes!<br>They try to use local or regional ingredients, lots of fresh herbs (some of which are home grown), and pack each dish full of flavour.<br>The service is impeccable and professional, but without the stiffness and formality you tend to find in fine dining. The atmosphere is relaxed and informal. This is all about the great food experience, and highly recommended.",
