"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"My aunt brought us here and I had currywurst for the first time. I ordered it with frites and mayonnaise to get the whole experience. I had a bit of a kebab, which was tasty. When I first heard about currywurst, I couldn&#39;t really wrap my head around the idea of curry powder with sausage and ketchup but once I tasted it, it made sense. The fries were nice and crispy but they were drowning in ketchup and mayo. I&#39;m only assuming that&#39;s how it&#39;s served traditionally because I don&#39;t have anything to compare it to. Despite the condiment drowning, I liked it anyway.<br><br>It was late at night on a weekday so there weren&#39;t a lot of people around besides a few couples and some guys stopping by for a quick bite after a night of drinking. They have tables that you stand at - no chairs here. Like other currywurst spots, it&#39;s very casual. My aunt and mom each had a bottle of Berliner Kindl Pilsner to accompany their food. Something I found interesting was that they have bottles of Moet in the fridge. You know, just in case you feel like popping bottles while snacking on sausage.<br><br>I don&#39;t know if this is THE place to go for currywurst but I really enjoyed the food here.",
