"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Yaam beach bar is a slice of the Caribbean in the middle of Berlin. Sitting just off the Spree in Friedrichshain, it&#39;s super easy to get to (it&#39;s a 2 minute walk from Ost Bahnhof).<br><br>It sits at the end of East Side Gallery, and is a great place to stroll along to after eyeing up some graffitti. Kick off your shoes and swap concrete for sand as you step inside its scribbled gates. Tucked behind multicoloured walls, you can lounge on a deckchair, in a hut or swing wildly on a hammock as you enjoy some strong (but tasty) cocktails.<br><br>It&#39;s a Caribbean cave of wonders, and you can wind down to the side of the Spree, which is bejewelled in fairylights, or prop up the bar and enjoy some of the reggae music during the evening.<br><br>Despite the fact Yaam throws a good party, there is a distinctive family vibe during the day. Its chilled out atmosphere is favoured by the locals, and its grassroots wackiness appeals to tourists. One of the highlights of a night in Berlin, Yaam is a vibrant, warm hearted alternative to a stuffy cocktail bar, any night of the week.",
