"reviewcomment":"Mauerpark is a great example of what makes Berlin different. Mauerpark is not a nice, manicured park, but it is lively, interesting and different, and of course it has a good stretch of the old Berlin wall running through it.<br>The history of the park is actually quite interesting. It was once the site of the Nordbahnhof (North Station) of Berlin, and continued to be a freight station up until the building of the Berlin wall. Afterwards, for obvious reasons the land became a mixture of death strip and waste land.<br>These day&#39;s the old death strip part is now the park, i.e. the grassy area and the hill, and the western part is now used for a flea market which is well worth visiting.",
