"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I was here earlier this week with my companion, as well as a couple of other companions. We had a reservation for 6 people at 8 PM, and we got this table right by the balcony. <br><br>When our party all arrived, the servers were quite attentive to all our needs. With 5 people and different food needs, the servers were more than happy to answer our questions (Q: What&#39;s Zigeune sauce? A: That&#39;s a sauce with plenty of Zigeune inside, finely chopped, very delicious!). Seriously, the servers were part entertainers. They seemed to be really enjoying their job. It was a very relaxed environment.<br><br>Okay, let me talk about the food. It was delicious. I had the artichoke appetizer, baked with goat cheese and vegetables. I shared this with my companion. And for my main dish, I got the roast rabbit. That was divine. Finally, my companion and I shared a half-liter of Greek dry red wine.<br><br>One thing I didn&#39;t like about this place is the quantity. Oh my god. Their food servings are huge. My appetizer (which was shared) was 6,50 EUR and comes in a huge plate. And my rabbit was 12,50 EUR and also came in a huge platter. Next time, I would share everything with someone, say, order one appetizer and one main dish to share. Because ideally, they would serve just 60% of the current quantity and reduce the price a little bit. But oh well, there&#39;s a way to trick the system. Hence, I am only giving this place 4 stars.",
