"reviewcomment":"After perusing Yelp to find a good Asian restaurant near Prenzlaurberg, I picked out Onkel Ho. Good reviews enticed me to it. My verdict is 4 stars. My husband and I really enjoyed the zen ambiance but I was not really impressed by the Pho. Firstly, they had a limited selection of pho. It was either chicken or beef so I ordered the beef soup. To me its a bit boring. I was looking for a combination of beef flank, tripe, tendon along with the beef steak (ohhh yeah I am a meat eater). Secondly, I thought that soup base was not as flavourful as the one I have elsewhere. I feel like it was missing a certain something (spicies or herbs) I cant quite figure out. Thirdly, since I am not so fond of sprouts, I was not too happy that the soup automatically came with it. I was so used to the separate plate of vegetables to accompany my soup. I am unsure if they provide fresh basil with the soup but I was not served with it.<br><br>On the other hand, my husband was impressed by the dish of the day which was vermicelli noodles and grilled beef topped with crushed peanut. They recalled it being juicy and tasty.<br><br>Overall, we were satisfied with out selections but I was not as impressed as my husband.",
