"reviewcomment":"Stopped in for lunch during my visit with my brother in Berlin.  The place was packed and we waited for a bit and then sat at the bar.<br><br>The bartender took our order as the waitress was hurrying around trying to get to everyone.  It didn&#39;t help that the beverage delivery was occurring during this lunch rush.  It was an inconvenience, but somehow added to the interesting buzzing vibe that was in the air.<br><br>Anyway, we started with a Michelada.  It was a good drink and the bartender added a bit more spice as I requested.<br><br>We also started with the Queso Fundido de Hongos.  It was a hot, gooey, tasty pot of molten cheese with mushrooms and other tasty treats.  To balance it out, we ordered the shrimp tacos, you know, to be a bit more healthy.  The tacos were also tasty and had good flavor.  The spicy chipotle cream had the right amount of spice.<br><br>Although it was busy and our order took a bit of time to come out, Santa Maria did not disappoint and the food definitely took care of the craving I had for Mexican.",
