"reviewcomment":"Fresh off a couple flights across the Atlantic, we needed fuel to begin our fight against jet lag.  We dropped our bags at our hotel and decided to explore the area.<br><br>A few blocks away, we stumbled upon SETs, with its open windows and tables pouring out onto the sidewalk.  It looked like a place to get a good lunch on a Sunday afternoon.  And it didn&#39;t let us down.<br><br>We sat inside, as all the outside tables were full, and we didn&#39;t want to wait.  Service was a little slow to get going, but not terrible.  I ordered a cappuccino, and was not disappointed (the first of many awesome cappuccinos in Germany).  Between the 4 of us, we got a huge salad, a ridiculously large club sandwich (with roasted turkey), and another equally large sandwich.  It was all fresh and delicious, and very filling.<br><br>Prices were reasonable - I think it was about 32 Euros for the whole deal.  If we were there for longer, we definitely would&#39;ve gone back.  Seems like a nice neighborhood spot.",
