"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Wow 5 stars from me but the fact that I went  here 3 times over 5 nights is Berlin should explain how much I enjoyed it here! <br><br>Situated in East Berlin, nicely tucked into the area of next to Warshauer strass U Bahn - Cass&#39; is in what can only be described as a compound of derelict warehouses, funky bars with no frills and a vibe that is laid back and independent. <br><br>With 3 big club rooms and 3 bars inside - everyone is catered for on a night out. On the weds night I went to see rapper Pharoahe Monch, Friday was all about 80&#39;s music/indie/rock and Hiphop while Saturday was more general cool tunes throughout with another favourite rapper &#39;Shabaam Sadeeq&#39; playing live in the main room. <br><br>Cloakrooms are €1, pints of excellent wheat beer €2.30 and the bouncers actually are a pleasure to chat to. If only this was how clubs operated back in the UK!<br><br>If you&#39;re in Berlin - you have to go here. Just check their website to see what&#39;s on in advance. Just be warned - the German guys on the fussball tables upstairs are absolute masters. No matter how good you think you are, you will get your arse kicked! We did...",
