"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"In a city that prides itself on it&#39;s casual nature, it&#39;s nice to run into a sophisticated place like Becketts Kopf.<br><br>You may think it&#39;s closed when you get there.  It&#39;s dark and the door will be shut.  If the scissor-gate is open, you&#39;re in luck!  Ring the bell and they&#39;ll look through the keyhole to see if they want your kind inside.  It&#39;s not as snooty as it sounds, as they let me in on a night that I looked like a drowned rat and my clothes were less than GQ worthy.  Doormen at techno clubs are harder to get past.<br><br>The place feels very cozy an private.  The music isn&#39;t blaring and it can&#39;t hold a huge throng of people.  The bartenders and staff are sophisticatedly dressed and very polite.  They have cool menus.  If you don&#39;t see what you&#39;re looking for, ask the bartender if he can make it.  They are absolute pros when it comes to mixed drinks; by far the best I&#39;ve seen and tasted in Berlin.  Ask the bartender to make you one of his favorites.<br><br>I would strongly recommend this place for entertaining an out-of-town client (cool client, not a goof), a nice place to talk to your date, or a nice place to go alone to enjoy a really good drink in a nice atmosphere.<br><br>I look forward to going back when I return to Berlin.",
