"reviewcomment":"The location is perfect. Across the street from the concert hall/opera house and within walking distance from Checkpoint Charlie, Brandenburger Tor, stores, restaurants and metro stations. It was easy to get to/from.<br><br>Two bell hops welcomed us and automatically took our bags to our room while we were checking in. This was nice since my luggage handle broke when I got it from Berlin airport. Check-in process was a breeze and there was a room available for us before the normal check-in time.<br><br>The hotel is an older but beautiful building. The lobby is pretty. There&#39;s a restaurant and a bar downstairs. There&#39;s free wifi at the lobby only. The room we had was nice and comfortable with a view of a chocolate shop! Toiletries include shampoo, conditioner, hand soap and body wash.<br><br>All the employees were helpful and polite. We had to check which channel the Real Madrid vs Bayern Munich was on and the concierge guy got the answer. I ended up watching the game at the lobby since there were lots of Munchen fans watching and I was the only Madrid fan - I&#39;m always ready for trash talking! After 2 goals from my team, people went back to their rooms. I really couldn&#39;t find a flaw with this hotel.",
