"reviewcomment":"I enjoyed seeing this site as it is so famous and known the world over. There isn&#39;t a lot to actually SEE, however and it does get very busy. Our hotel was just around the corner so it was nice to walk and pass by it on a daily basis while in Berlin. The museum located nearby is the main attraction for me - it is a history of the wall and is eye-opening and enlightening. The museum looks like it&#39;ll be small from the outside, but don&#39;t be fooled! It can take a long time to look around but is well worth it.<br><br>We often saw this area in the evening as well, when going back to our hotel. This is a great time to have a second look around and think, as there is next to nobody about later on.<br><br>It&#39;s definitely a must-see, due to the historical significance of the area, but don&#39;t expect to spend a lot of time here. Maybe grab a coffee afterwards!",
