"reviewcomment":"Baraka is an excellent choice in the Kreuzberg neighborhood for Middle Eastern / Egyptian food. I usually stop by here at least once when I&#39;m in the city. Great food, nice interior, and good service!<br><br>Pro&#39;s:<br><br>- creative interior (cloudesque ceilings) and authentic furniture (low tables, chairs, and sofas)<br>- tapas-style food that comes in dozens of small bowls<br>- main dishes are usually served with bread on the side and hummus<br>- good food quality, inexpensive ... great value for money<br><br>Con&#39;s:<br><br>- furniture needs some overhaul<br><br>There is also a takeaway window in case you want to grab a Shawarma to go. I usually sit down and get something grilled (lamb or chicken) with rice and several sides (hummus, vegetables, beans). I like the variety of dishes and drinks (try the Mango Lassi). If you&#39;re in the mood for Middle Eastern - this is your place!",
