"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I am somebody who has always been fascinated by the war and this was at the top of my to-do list when I visted Berlin.<br><br>The exhibition is built among the ruins of the old SS headquarters and this certainly adds an extra poignancy.<br><br>There is a large area outside which is a timeline of the rise of the Nazis. It is essentially a straight line with informative boards placed in sequence. Take your time to let the information sink in, don&#39;t rush along!<br><br>At the end we thought that was it... we were wrong. There&#39;s an equally fantastic exhibition in the indoor section located at the end of the walk. Make sure to do this, I can&#39;t rate it highly enough.<br><br>This indoor part goes into even more detail and is extremely chilling. It is important that this story is shared and understood and I think it is a very brave thing to have such a prominent display tackling it.<br><br>A must-see.",
