"rating":"2.5",
"reviewcomment":"I have heard people rave about how cheap and fashionable Primark is, so I finally got the chance to check it out, and even though it seems to get a lot of hate, I think I am a fan.<br><br>True, there were a lot of people on a weekday and there was an air of chaos, but I just avoided the crazed teenagers who were killing time after school as best I could.<br><br>I didn&#39;t try on any of the clothes, so I can&#39;t speak to them. But I did get some accessories that were cute and incredibly cheap, like sunglasses, scarves, socks, and undies. I only hope that the quality is better than some people suggest, but time will tell.<br><br>It would be nice if there was more than one Primark in Berlin, although I can eventually see that happening. Even so, the location in Steglitz is a good choice, as it&#39;s along a shopping street. I have heard rumors of ethical concerns, however, so I think I would like to read up on those before returning.",
