"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Went to this Amrit @ Winderfeldtplatz in August...Didn&#39;t want to like it too much since it is a chain restaurant, but alas, they definitely won me over.  I LOVED the food...it was probably some of the best Indian food I have ever had (and trust me..I know my Indian food pretty well).<br><br>Sometimes you feel you need to go to a hole-in-the-wall place to get &#34;authentic&#34; ethnic food... some place off the beaten path, less pretentious looking,etc... but that is not the case with Amrit.  First of all it is a BEAUTIFUL restaurant.  Especially nice in the warmer months, when you sit outside...but regardless it&#39;s great.  Secondly, the prices are awesome, for such great quality food and generous portions.<br><br>Yummy lamb saag, curried chicken, rice, naan, bhathura, dipping sauces, cocktails, King Fisher beer (pilsner)... everything we ate/drank that evening rocked from start to finish.  I even had leftovers bagged up to take home... so that should indicate a) how good the food was and b)how nice the portions were.<br><br>SUGGESTIONS:  Why can&#39;t I get some good gulab jamun in Berlin, generally?  <br><br>VERDICT:  If you like Indian food and need a good fix, this is the place.  Great for families, singles, dates, taking visitors, etc.   I&#39;m definitely a fan and will definitely be heading back next time I crave some good Indian food in a nice restaurant....",
