"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I love this place.<br><br> Like Koernerpark in Neukoelln, it&#39;s just such a complete surprise to find a true urban oasis smack in the middle of an otherwise not terribly compelling part of town. Also like Koernerpark, the pond/fountain is below street level, so traffic noise is minimal.<br><br> I sat here today, enjoyed a yummy toast and Bionade, while listening to the fountains and watching two turtles sunbathe on the small rocks at the edge of the Cafe&#39;s deck.<br><br> The menu is limited, but service was good (possibly less so if filled to capacitythere are quite a few tables, although only about 8 on the prime deck area in front of the cafe itself -- which is, interestingly, formed from several joined metal containers, such as you would find at a construction site).<br><br> Although not as lushly planted as some other urban nature spots, I highly recommend Engelbecken for a respite from sirens, S-bahn rumblings, and traffic noise.",
