"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/Ed0yJMz2-yks0dhfghCdjg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"First things first: MAKE A RESERVATION.<br><br>Yes I know it&#39;s just mini-golf, and you&#39;ve only got 4 people. It&#39;s the middle of the week at 5:30pm. You should be able to just walk right in. But you&#39;d be entirely wrong. Hit up the website and click on &#34;RESERVIERUNG&#34; in the menu.<br><br>Now, how do you actually find the place? I&#39;m pretty sure a disgruntled hipster wizard cast a spell on this place to make it nigh un-findable. The quick version is to simply enter the park from the Görlitzer Bahnhof U-Bahn station and it&#39;ll be the very first building you approach if you keep to the path. Enter on the right side.<br><br>The mini-golf itself, once you manage to snag a reservation and get yourself inside, is pretty damn fun. It&#39;s black-lit with 3D and makes for a super fun experience with friends. At only 6.50 EUR, it&#39;s also a bargain for 1-2 hours of sweaty, eye-straining excitement.<br><br>Not that it doesn&#39;t come without its caveats. The staff, well it would be kind to say they&#39;re simply curt. Your experience may vary from general indifference to downright rudeness. The maintenance of the holes themselves is also merely a suggestion. The last four holes will make you angry at the world.",
