"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"I&#39;ve eaten here a couple of times. Around 6-7 i would say. <br>I love their food, it&#39;s simple and delicious.<br><br>Their smoothies are a little boring, but i like their menucard detail where they tell you which smoothie is good for what, nice detail. <br><br>Their sushi is great! It&#39;s not the most creative or surprising sushi, but it&#39;s very good and satisfying. I could always eat their avocado-sushi, yum! And they have a little fun feature where you can select Kappa-rolls with either yellow, blue, pink, spotted or green, nori-wrapping, so cute.  <br><br>Last time i was there I got the Vegan duck in red curry. It was awesome! It could have used some more vegetables though, but other than that- Perfect. Very mild, with a nice red curry flavor, and the mockduck is so crispy and delicious! And with a smallish portion of rice, so you don&#39;t feel like they cheap out and make it 70% rice/30% other. The only thing it needed was more veggies. <br>The menu says that it&#39;s &#34;strong/Spicy&#34; which i wouldn&#39;t say, so be sure to tell them you want it extra &#34;scharf&#34; if that&#39;s what you&#39;re into :) <br><br>I&#39;ve gotta admit that i was close to bumping Papa nô down to a 3 because the service is bad, but the food is so nice. <br>The staff comes off lazy and uninterested in giving a good service. They are VERY impatient, and never smile. And they just call you when your food is ready even though it&#39;s a large restaurant with a pretty &#34;fancy&#34; look. <br>The person accompanying me on one of my visits does not speak or read german, and therefore made the mistake of looking in the &#34;only for take-out orders&#34;-fridge for a beer that he could buy. When the staff saw this all 3 started yelling at us in German, making it impossible for me to translate for him what he should do instead, pretty buttholish of them. <br><br>All in all<br>2 for the service<br>but 4 for the food :)",
