"reviewcomment":"This hotel has more personality than any other hotel I have ever seen. It is hard to explain, you just have to experience it. Though you might get an idea from visiting the website or from hearing that they will deliver a Gibson guitar to your room via room service.<br><br>I stayed here for a conference last week and I really enjoyed my stay. The beds were very comfrotable, the room amenitites (slippers, toiltetries, etc) were nice. The view of the river Spree is great, especially from the higher floors. <br><br>The best part of the hotel is that the staff and many of the services are at the level of a truly fine hotel (St Regis, Ritz Carlton, Four Seasons). I am not saying the hotel is that nice - it isn&#39;t.  It is more like a W level than a St Regis level. But the staff is that friendly, professional and helpful. The concierge was outstanding.  Working with the concierge Jan was no different than working with a concierge at one of the  best hotels in the world. Laundry/dry cleaning and room service were also top-notch in both friendliness, promptness and product.<br><br>The conference I spoke at paid for my room and I am not sure what the rate was, but I understand it was reasonable. Wifi was free to all guests. It did pay for room service, drinks in the bar and laundry service, and they were all very reasonably priced. So I think this hotel is a great value.",
