"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I rarely go to bars, so I don&#39;t have a high bar for bar reviews. Anyway, this was the site of a meet-up event tonight, and at 7:45 PM, the place was still slow. That was the time when I walked in and saw a couple of friends. <br><br>I ordered a White Russian. I didn&#39;t know it was a recommended thing here. I just wanted something potent and with Kahlua in it. But it was very potent. I ordered a second, and soon enough, I was swimming in bliss. Perhaps the good company was also to blame, but I did have a good time. <br><br>So why just 4 stars? Well, when you need to go to the toilet, well, it&#39;s downstairs. In some sort of Gothic looking area. In a stale musty part of the establishment. No wonder nobody is down there, and everybody is upstairs. Unfortunately, the sofas are downstairs. But it seemed like it is just inhabited by ghosts, and if you have just finished a horror Gothic novel like me, then it&#39;s probably creepy. Good thing I only went to the toilet once.<br><br>Anyway, I&#39;ll be back, as they never seem to be conservative when it comes to alcohol in their cocktails. Very potent.",
