"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Berlin is one of my favourite  European cities without a doubt. It has countless cool things to see, places to eat and trendy areas to hang out in. <br>Some of the more up and coming areas are in the East side of Berlin and that is where you find this cool little restaurant/bar. We had been going for a saunter up Karl Marx Alley  and at one point turned off it and after a few more turns ended up here.<br><br>We had the breakfast platter to share. It was HUGE and really reasonably priced. There was an abundance of cold meats, cheeses , breads, eggs and fruit. To go along side that I had a great vanilla milk shake. Due to over indulgence on the alcohol front the night before, I was feeling a bit sensitive and this sorted me right out. <br>The decor inside the place is nice and the location is great . Only slight moan was the service was quite slow, but there was lots of plus points that meant I could generally overlook this.",
