"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Yogi-Haus is one of the better places in Berlin to get some decent Indian fare. It&#39;s family-owned and their cooking is consistent. Their generous portions are served by some of the nicest and most helpful servers in the city. It&#39;s almost always filled with locals, though those from the Indian sub-continent are missing.<br><br> 1. The Food<br>Well prepared standard Indian fare, with vegetarian options. Some dishes are on the oily/greasy side. The dishes are not very spicy, most likely because of their customer base, but are tinkered with on request. Their food is better seasoned than most Indian places in the city, with the brightness of their curries balanced out with the creaminess of their ghee and cream.<br><br> 2. The Staff <br>Kind, easy-going and quick.<br><br> 3. The atmosphere<br>A local neighbourhood hang-out. They also have a nice heated patio where you can sip on their numerous cocktails throughout the year.<br><br> 4. The damage<br>Most dishes are under 7 euros. Drinks are 2-5.<br><br> 5. Useful tidbits<br>Try their platter of mixed appetisers or creamy mango lassi.",
