"reviewcomment":"My companions and I went here for lunch yesterday. As one of them wanted some good Indian food, I asked for recommendations from the interwebs, and Kifah told me that this is one of the better Indian restaurants here in Berlin.<br><br>They open from noon, which was the time we were there. We ordered two different appetizers (and they were more than happy to accommodate us in asking for an extra samosa, as we were three), as well as three different main dishes. Unfortunately, they didn&#39;t have naan, simply because they just opened for the day, and that meant that their stone oven for making naan isn&#39;t ready yet. Understandable. <br><br>The main dishes were quite lovely. And what I liked the most, is that they never toned down their flavors to accommodate the cowardly German palate. Spicy things are indeed spicy. So that lamb curry was definitely potent!<br><br>I would definitely come back here again, perhaps even for dinner, when they have naan. I gladly give this place 5 stars, and I promise to be back.",
