"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/d0rz73dM6aAf3Yt7lVeMQA/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I knew that today was going to be a long day (yes, I am writing this review during the 10 minutes free time that I found this late afternoon). I was in my office since before 9:00 AM and will be here until around 6:00 PM. So around mid-afternoon, I took a break and took some papers I needed to read, while trying to find a new cafe. I found the Sarotti Höfe, named after the chocolatier Sarotti. <br><br>True to the name, they offer plenty of chocolate-related drinks, both alcoholic and non-alcoholic. The temperature was a little chilly, so I asked for a grog and a slice of the sachertorte. That set me back 6,80 EUR. And yes, I enjoyed it, in many ways.<br><br>The grog was potent. The sachertorte was chocolatey. And I was light-headed after consuming these two items and walking back to my office. <br><br>I give this place 4 stars. Perhaps it&#39;s because I like the interior: it has charm and character, and gives off an old-world feel, at the same time making people of all walks of life welcome (they have a rainbow sticker at the door, among other things). I also like the plentiful choices of cakes. What I don&#39;t like is the lack of accessible electric plugs. So this isn&#39;t a place I would like to set up a laptop and work in, this is more a place where one would feel comfortable taking a little break from the hustle and bustle of life and sip a drink, potent or non-potent.",
