"categorystrlist":"Cuban,         Cocktail Bars",
"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/s0SMJij9vHFX7fZFha6-xg/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"While this place is a restaurant, this review only applies for the drinks. My companion and I headed here after dinner last night because we wanted mojitos. So why not go to a Cuban place for it? <br><br>They are sort of a restaurant, sort of a bar. They have both a food menu and a drink menu. And their drink menu was enormous too, I almost regretted not sampling the other offerings. Though I have to say, the mojitos were very potent. Very potent that I was very tempted to order another one, if not for a pressing appointment later that night. So I settled for just one.<br><br>The place has a dark atmosphere; it is more a cavern-like dive bar than a restaurant. That being said, the acoustics are good enough to allow you to have a conversation with your companions. <br><br>The service was great; the staff regularly checked on us whether we were doing okay or whether we needed anything else. And yes, they were very visually appealing, which fuels one&#39;s imagination, to the point that I almost wished I took Spanish instead of German when I was taking foreign language courses in the university, just so that I can carry a longer conversation with them while visually appreciating them. I guess the mojitos were partly to blame.",
