"reviewcomment":"I discovered this place today and will definitely come back many times for their &#34;crazy hour&#34; - an all-you-can-eat sushi (and other dishes) buffet between 15h and 17h every day for only 7,90 euro - unbelievably cheap.<br><br> As far as I could tell, the sushi was good, though the sake nigiri had more white fat in it than usual. It&#39;s all very fresh - the chef comes out with more pieces all the time, so you know they haven&#39;t been lying there all day. I also had a very tender pangasius filet and a delicious fried banana for dessert - all included in the buffet price.<br><br> Lots of people sharing the huge tables - each of them has a built in grill where the chef can come out and cook directly in front of the guests, something that happens only in the evenings I suppose.<br><br> 1/2 liter tap beer: 4 euro.<br><br> À la carte prices are about 15 euro per dish I think, and there are also quite elaborate menues for more persons - that&#39;s probably when the table grills are used.",
