"reviewcomment":"Food: delicious. The burger was impeccable--my only complaint was the relatively low quality lettuce and tomato, and less onion strings than I would&#39;ve liked. But those honeyed figs... DANG. I got &#34;The Egyptian,&#34; and would recommend it a thousand times over.<br><br>Drinks: The one and only place I&#39;ve ever had a satisfactory Gin cocktail. Still a bigger fan of whiskey--and they have that too--but it was on their specials list, and was definitely a good pick!<br><br>Atmosphere: Music: Great choice of jazzy pop covers, at just the right volume. Service: fantastic--they even took my coat and let us stay a little past our reservation. A little surprised when we got served by a dude in a dress (this is after all in the heart of Berlin&#39;s gay district), but hey, it&#39;s a free country!<br><br>The bill: less expensive than I would have thought, but then again we&#39;re talking Euros and I haven&#39;t gotten over the exchange difference... So, maybe a little pricy. 20€ including tip.<br><br>Final Statement: AMAZING burgers, good drinks (if the beer selection is a bit sparse, the bar is fantastic), great service, slightly unusual locale. Four stars, minus one for the lackluster condiments. But only just!",
