"reviewcomment":"If you want to get away from the busy wasteland of consumerism and tourism that is Alexanderplatz, the Nikolaiviertel is a refreshing piece of Berlin history. Founded in 1200, this is the original old Berlin (Alt-Berlin, if you will). And though it&#39;s just a hop, skip, and a jump away from Alex, the architecture and the overall ambiance are totally different. <br><br>Granted, this is also a popular destination for visitors, but it manages to still retain a bit of charm. Truth be told, Nikolaiviertel is best experienced on a weekday afternoon in the spring. Stroll around the cobblestone streets, admire the buildings, peek into shops, or grab a beer and sit alongside the river. While it&#39;s never a destination, whenever I find myself here, I can&#39;t help but enjoy it.",
