"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"This modern European bistro is located a few blocks away from where I live. They were also open early. Hence, when we needed brunch, this was a place we decided to try.<br><br>They serve brunch from 8:00 AM to 3:00 PM. They have several types of &#34;breakfast platters&#34; but given the amount of stuff in there, they are more brunch than breakfast. Perhaps I am just used to the idea of a small breakfast, and the things they offer look like lunch to me. <br><br>My companion got the Italian breakfast, which consists of several types of cured meat, cheese, an egg, and many other goodies. I on the other hand got the salmon omelette. They both come with complimentary bread, which definitely looked fresh. <br><br>The food was great, but the drinks were spectacular. I whole-heartedly recommend the &#34;Kaffee al Sheikh&#34; which is this shot of espresso, made with Arabian spices and cardamom. It&#39;s strong, bitter, and they serve it with a glass of water on the side, but it is amazing. It&#39;s a coffee experience. I also recommend the &#34;Karkadee Tee&#34; which I tried the next day, which is a herbal tea made from Egyptian herbs and spices.<br><br>Yes, things were so good here we decided to pay them a visit again the next day. So yes, this place gets 5 stars in my book. It is definitely as good as it gets.",
