"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/076xxpejV4eFo-S5IE6sMQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"Potatoes potatoes potatoes! Seriously, if you are a spuds fan, this restaurant is for you. I was in Berlin last fall for a work conference and a few of us stopped in here for dinner our first night. Since I didn&#39;t have Yelp Germany to rely on at that time, I had to count on my good friend Google (and Google translate) to help me scope out some spots before we left the states. My co-workers were grateful that I had come prepared and had some idea of the places that were in the vicinity of our hotel and the conference center. This place was the first stop on our list, and it definitely impressed.<br><br>The food seemed to  be typical German fare (based solely on one other prior visit to this fine city). Lots of pork. And endless potatoes, in any variety you could imagine. I went with the roasted pork with saurkraut and potato dumplings. Very filling, and very delicious. <br><br>Aside from the food, this is a good spot just for the interior ambiance. Very cute and homey decor. There were also an interesting variety of eclectic trinkets and wall hangings that kept us entertained throughout the night each time we spotted a new one. <br><br>If you&#39;re looking for something light, you should probably look elsewhere. But, if you&#39;re in the mood fora hearty German meal, look no further, this place will have what you need!",
