"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"I was here with a companion after work, as it was time to catch up. We originally planned to try another bar, yet we found out that it was a smoker&#39;s-only bar, so we searched for another one. We ended up here.<br><br>It was a Wednesday evening, and so it wasn&#39;t crowded. There was a toddler on the bar. I got a beer, while my companion ordered a hot chocolate, as he was moving away from alcohol for the time being due to a headache. Oh, we also ordered nuts.<br><br>I like the ambiance. I like the huge selection of drinks. They also have food, but it would be great if they have more finger food. Based on the menu, all they have a cheese of various sorts on bread. And nachos. <br><br>That being said, I would consider coming back here again. It&#39;s on a dead end in Mitte, which makes the place rather quiet, and the experience of catching up and shooting the breeze in a tucked-away place is quaint at times.",
