"reviewcomment":"On a recent trip to Berlin with 25 people, it was safe to say that finding space for our group was getting more and more difficult as the nights went on. With us planning on going to the nearby Cassiopeia later on, the trusty Yelp app helped me find this bar which was just up a side street and tucked away - in fact there wasn&#39;t even a sign outside telling you the name of it and most of it was covered in scaffolding (very Berlin - could be a cool permanent thing!)<br><br>Inside there was a DJ spinning quality classic chilled grooves, the bar staff were friendly and welcoming to us Brits and as usual for Berlin, the costs of the beer didn&#39;t set you back more than €2.50. The interior is all red leather and is a maze of small rooms, passages and cubby holes - a real cave of a place but it&#39;s surprisingly spacious. with loads of room in the back if there&#39;s a big group of you. <br><br>Overall a great find and one that sorted us out for a few hours before a heavy night of clubbing - sweet!",
